⚠️ EXPLICIT VARIABLE TYPES REQUIRED:
All variables MUST have explicit type annotations.

This project does not rely on type inference - all types must be explicit.

❌ NEVER omit variable types:
```typescript
// ❌ BAD: Implicit types
const user = { id: '1', name: 'John' };
let count = 0;
const items = [];
const result = await fetch('/api/data');
```

✅ ALWAYS specify explicit types:
```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Explicit types
const user: User = new User('1', 'John');
let count: number = 0;
const items: Item[] = [];
const result: Response = await fetch('/api/data');

// ✅ GOOD: Explicit array types
const numbers: number[] = [1, 2, 3];
const users: User[] = [];
const matrix: number[][] = [[1, 2], [3, 4]];

// ✅ GOOD: Explicit object types (prefer classes)
const config: DatabaseConfig = {
  host: 'localhost',
  port: 5432,
  database: 'mydb',
};

// ✅ GOOD: Explicit union types
const status: 'active' | 'inactive' | 'pending' = 'active';
const value: string | number = 42;

// ✅ GOOD: Explicit promise types
const userPromise: Promise<User> = fetchUser('123');

// ✅ GOOD: Explicit function types
const handler: (event: Event) => void = (event: Event): void => {
  console.log(event);
};

// ✅ GOOD: Explicit Map/Set types
const userMap: Map<string, User> = new Map();
const uniqueIds: Set<string> = new Set();

// ✅ GOOD: Explicit Record types
const config: Record<string, string> = {
  apiKey: 'xxx',
  endpoint: 'https://api.example.com',
};
```

**Type annotation guidelines:**
  - Always specify types on const/let/var declarations
  - Use specific types, not general ones (User not object)
  - Prefer classes over plain object types
  - Specify array element types: Type[] or Array<Type>
  - Specify generic types: Map<K, V>, Set<T>, Promise<T>
  - Use union types for multiple possibilities: Type1 | Type2
  - Use literal types for constants: 'value' not string

**Exceptions (still discouraged):**
  - Primitive literals in obvious contexts: `const x: number = 1;`
  - But prefer: `const X: number = 1;` (explicit constant)

See: .claude/rules/strict-typing-class-patterns.md
